## Germplasm Phenotype:
   - [gaut5-1 gaut6-1 gaut7-1]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;Homozygous triple mutant: seed failed to be produced, indicating that male gametophytic transmissiong through mutant pollen is inhibited during cross pollination, confirming a role of all three genes in male fertility. Heterozygous triple mutant: most pollen does not germinate, nearly half of pollen that does germinate diplays bursting tubes.
